    "organization": "Neilsoft Ltd.",
    "category": "Software",
    "description": "<table id=\"settings\" class=\"table table-bordered table-hover\">\n                        <thead>\n                        <tr>\n                            <th style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Problem Statement ID</th>\n                            <td>\n                                <div class=\"style-2\" style=\"overflow-y: auto; min-height:20px; max-height: 200px; width:100%;\"> 25259</div>\n                               </td>\n                            </tr>\n                        <tr>\n                            <th style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Problem Statement Title</th>\n                            <td>\n                                <div class=\"style-2\" style=\"overflow-y: auto; min-height:20px; max-height: 200px; width:100%;\"> Recovery and reuse of Fresh water resources</div>\n                               </td>\n                            </tr>\n                            <tr>\n                            <th style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Description</th>\n                            <td>\n                                <!-- <div class=\"style-2\" style=\"overflow-y: auto; min-height:20px; max-height: 200px; width:100%;\"> &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Problem Statement:&lt;/b&gt; Reuse of water resources are basic to sustaining human life, agriculture, industry and the ecosystem.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Background:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nFresh water being an increasingly valuable resource, most industrial processes rely on fresh water, which often results in a wastewater stream. Addressing the growing need of fresh water challenges that industries are facing, including waste and pollution minimization, water scarcity, compliance with legislation and economic circularity of water is the key to the survival of life.\n&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Expected Solution:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nThis problem statement proposes the design of a Smart Process System design for separation and cleaning at primary (solid removal), secondary (organic removal), and tertiary (nutrient and advanced contaminant removal) treatment stages, with the level of treatment determined by the intended reuse.\n&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Impact:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nThis sustainable practice conserves freshwater resources, reduces environmental impact, and is very important for water-scarce regions. This will improve Water conservation, Resource recovery &amp;amp; support Circular economy by Recycle, Reduce and Reuse of Water.\n&lt;/p&gt;</div> -->\n                                 <div class=\"style-2\" style=\"overflow-y: auto; min-height:20px; max-height: 200px; width:100%;\"> <p><b>Problem Statement:</b> Reuse of water resources are basic to sustaining human life, agriculture, industry and the ecosystem.</p>\n\n<p><b>Background:</b><br>\nFresh water being an increasingly valuable resource, most industrial processes rely on fresh water, which often results in a wastewater stream. Addressing the growing need of fresh water challenges that industries are facing, including waste and pollution minimization, water scarcity, compliance with legislation and economic circularity of water is the key to the survival of life.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>Expected Solution:</b><br>\nThis problem statement proposes the design of a Smart Process System design for separation and cleaning at primary (solid removal), secondary (organic removal), and tertiary (nutrient and advanced contaminant removal) treatment stages, with the level of treatment determined by the intended reuse.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>Impact:</b><br>\nThis sustainable practice conserves freshwater resources, reduces environmental impact, and is very important for water-scarce regions. This will improve Water conservation, Resource recovery &amp; support Circular economy by Recycle, Reduce and Reuse of Water.\n</p></div>\n                               </td>\n                            </tr>\n\n                            <tr>\n                                <th>Organization</th>\n                            <td>Neilsoft Ltd. </td>\n                                            \n                            </tr>  \n                            \n                            <tr>\n                                <th>Department</th>\n                            <td>\n                                Neilsoft Ltd. \n                                <!-- echo $user_info->department;  -->\n                            </td>\n                                            \n                            </tr>  \n\n                            <tr>\n                            <th>Category</th>\n                            <td>Software</td>\n                            </tr>\n\n                            <tr>\n                            <th>Theme</th>\n                            <td>Clean &amp; Green Technology</td>\n                            </tr>\n                            <tr>\n                              <th>Youtube Link</th>\n                              <td>\n                                    <a href=\" \" target=\"_blank\"> </a>\n                            </td>  \n                            </tr> \n                          <!--                             <tr>\n                              <th>Dataset Link</th>\n                              <td>\n                                \n                                    <br>\n                                     <a href=\"\"><br></a>\n                                 <a href=\"https://www.sih.gov.in/dataset/\"><br></a>\n                                                                                          </td>  \n                            </tr> -->\n                                                                <tr>\n                                    <th>Dataset Link</th>\n                                    <td>\n                                                                            </td>\n                                    </tr>\n\n                            <tr>\n                              <th>Contact info</th>\n                              <td>\n                                    <a href=\" \" target=\"_blank\"> </a>\n                            </td>  \n                            </tr> \n    \n                      </thead>\n                     </table>",
