    "category": "Hardware",
    "description": "<table id=\"settings\" class=\"table table-bordered table-hover\">\n                        <thead>\n                        <tr>\n                            <th style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Problem Statement ID</th>\n                            <td>\n                                <div class=\"style-2\" style=\"overflow-y: auto; min-height:20px; max-height: 200px; width:100%;\"> 25266</div>\n                               </td>\n                            </tr>\n                        <tr>\n                            <th style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Problem Statement Title</th>\n                            <td>\n                                <div class=\"style-2\" style=\"overflow-y: auto; min-height:20px; max-height: 200px; width:100%;\"> Low-Cost machinery for picking of cotton.\n\n</div>\n                               </td>\n                            </tr>\n                            <tr>\n                            <th style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Description</th>\n                            <td>\n                                <!-- <div class=\"style-2\" style=\"overflow-y: auto; min-height:20px; max-height: 200px; width:100%;\"> &lt;b&gt;Background&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Cotton cultivation in India is predominantly carried out by small and marginal farmers, who constitute over 70% of the farming population, Manual cotton picking is labour-intensive, time-consuming, and increasingly challenged by labour shortages and rising costs. Mechanized solutions available in the market are often unaffordable and unsuitable for small landholdings.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Design and develop a low-cost, portable, and efficient cotton-picking machine tailored for small and marginal farmers. The machine should:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Operate effectively in fragmented and uneven cotton fields.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be lightweight and easy to handle by a single user.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Minimize damage to cotton bolls and plants.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be powered by battery or solar energy for rural deployment.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Picked Cotton with minimum trash content.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Proposed Innovation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;A compact, semi-automated cotton-picking device equipped with:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Al-powered vision system (using Open CV and Tensor Flow) to detect mature cotton bolls.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Storage compartment for collected cotton.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Modular design for easy maintenance and scalability.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Benefits&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Reduces dependency on manual labour.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Enhances picking efficiency and speed.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Improves cotton quality by minimizing contamination.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Empowers small farmers with affordable mechanization.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Implementation Scope&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;This solution can be piloted in cotton-growing regions of the country. It aligns with the goals of Atmanirbhar Bharat and Digital India by promoting indigenous, tech-enabled agricultural tools.</div> -->\n                                 <div class=\"style-2\" style=\"overflow-y: auto; min-height:20px; max-height: 200px; width:100%;\"> <b>Background</b><br>Cotton cultivation in India is predominantly carried out by small and marginal farmers, who constitute over 70% of the farming population, Manual cotton picking is labour-intensive, time-consuming, and increasingly challenged by labour shortages and rising costs. Mechanized solutions available in the market are often unaffordable and unsuitable for small landholdings.<br><br><b>Description</b><br>Design and develop a low-cost, portable, and efficient cotton-picking machine tailored for small and marginal farmers. The machine should:<br><ol><li>Operate effectively in fragmented and uneven cotton fields.</li><li>Be lightweight and easy to handle by a single user.</li><li>Minimize damage to cotton bolls and plants.</li><li>Be powered by battery or solar energy for rural deployment.</li><li>Picked Cotton with minimum trash content.</li></ol><br><b>Proposed Innovation</b><br>A compact, semi-automated cotton-picking device equipped with:<br><ol><li>Al-powered vision system (using Open CV and Tensor Flow) to detect mature cotton bolls.</li><li>Storage compartment for collected cotton.</li><li>Modular design for easy maintenance and scalability.</li></ol><br><b>Benefits</b><br><ol><li>Reduces dependency on manual labour.</li><li>Enhances picking efficiency and speed.</li><li>Improves cotton quality by minimizing contamination.</li><li>Empowers small farmers with affordable mechanization.</li></ol><br><b>Implementation Scope</b><br>This solution can be piloted in cotton-growing regions of the country. It aligns with the goals of Atmanirbhar Bharat and Digital India by promoting indigenous, tech-enabled agricultural tools.</div>\n                               </td>\n                            </tr>\n\n                            <tr>\n                                <th>Organization</th>\n                            <td>Ministry of Agriculture &amp; Farmers Welfare (MoA&amp;FW) </td>\n                                            \n                            </tr>  \n                            \n                            <tr>\n                                <th>Department</th>\n                            <td>\n                                Department of Agriculture &amp; Farmers Welfare (DoA&amp;FW) (Crops) \n                                <!-- echo $user_info->department;  -->\n                            </td>\n                                            \n                            </tr>  \n\n                            <tr>\n                            <th>Category</th>\n                            <td>Hardware</td>\n                            </tr>\n\n                            <tr>\n                            <th>Theme</th>\n                            <td>Agriculture, FoodTech &amp; Rural Development</td>\n                            </tr>\n                            <tr>\n                              <th>Youtube Link</th>\n                              <td>\n                                    <a href=\" \" target=\"_blank\"> </a>\n                            </td>  \n                            </tr> \n                          <!--                             <tr>\n                              <th>Dataset Link</th>\n                              <td>\n                                \n                                    <br>\n                                     <a href=\"\"><br></a>\n                                 <a href=\"https://www.sih.gov.in/dataset/\"><br></a>\n                                                                                          </td>  \n                            </tr> -->\n                                                                <tr>\n                                    <th>Dataset Link</th>\n                                    <td>\n                                                                            </td>\n                                    </tr>\n\n                            <tr>\n                              <th>Contact info</th>\n                              <td>\n                                    <a href=\" \" target=\"_blank\"> </a>\n                            </td>  \n                            </tr> \n    \n                      </thead>\n                     </table>",
