    "description": "<table id=\"settings\" class=\"table table-bordered table-hover\">\n                        <thead>\n                        <tr>\n                            <th style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Problem Statement ID</th>\n                            <td>\n                                <div class=\"style-2\" style=\"overflow-y: auto; min-height:20px; max-height: 200px; width:100%;\"> 1790</div>\n                               </td>\n                            </tr>\n                        <tr>\n                            <th style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Problem Statement Title</th>\n                            <td>\n                                <div class=\"style-2\" style=\"overflow-y: auto; min-height:20px; max-height: 200px; width:100%;\"> Face Recognition Surveillance System and Communication Systems for Missing Persons or Items at Simhastha Ujjain for the Police Department</div>\n                               </td>\n                            </tr>\n                            <tr>\n                            <th style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Description</th>\n                            <td>\n                                <div class=\"style-2\" style=\"overflow-y: auto; min-height:20px; max-height: 200px; width:100%;\"> Simhastha Ujjain, one of the largest religious gatherings in India, witnesses millions of pilgrims and tourists congregating in a single location. Managing such a vast crowd poses significant challenges for the police department, particularly in ensuring the safety and security of individuals and locating missing persons or items. The deployment of advanced technologies like face recognition surveillance systems and efficient communication systems is critical to address these challenges.\n Issues Faced\n 1. High Volume of Missing Persons and Items:\n ├ö├ç├│ Overwhelming Number of Reports: During Simhasth, the number of reports for missing persons and items surges, making it difficult for the police to manage and respond promptly.\n ├ö├ç├│ Identification Challenges: Identifying missing persons in a vast, densely populated area is challenging without advanced technology.\n 2. Inefficient Manual Processes:\n ├ö├ç├│ Time-Consuming Identification: Traditional methods of identifying missing persons through manual verification of photos and descriptions are time-consuming and prone to errors.\n ├ö├ç├│ Delayed Response: The manual process leads to delayed response times, reducing the chances of quickly locating missing persons or items.\n 3. Communication Barriers:\n ├ö├ç├│ Lack of Real-Time Updates: Communication between different units and officers is often delayed, affecting coordination and timely response.\n ├ö├ç├│ Inefficient Information Dissemination: The absence of a centralized system to disseminate information about missing persons or items hampers effective communication and coordination.\n 4. Security Concerns:\n ├ö├ç├│ Crowd Control: Managing and monitoring large crowds to prevent and respond to incidents is challenging without real-time surveillance and communication.\n ├ö├ç├│ Potential Threats: The risk of criminal activities increases in such large gatherings. necessitating advanced surveillance for timely threat detection and intervention.\n Impact on Operations\n 1. Reduced Efficiency: The inability to quickly and accurately identify and locate missing persons or items results in reduced operational efficiency and effectiveness.\n 2. Public Safety Risks: Delays in responding to reports of missing persons or items pose significant safety risks, especially for vulnerable individuals such as children or the elderly.\n 3. Increased Operational Burden: The police department faces an increased burden due to the high volume of cases and the need for extensive manual effort.\n 4. Eroded Public Trust: Inefficient handling of missing persons or items can erode public trust in the police department's ability to ensure safety and security during large events.\n Solution Requirements:\n 1. Face Recognition Surveillance System:\n ├ö├ç├│ Real-Time Identification: Deploy face recognition technology to identify and track missing persons in real-time from surveillance footage.\n ├ö├ç├│ Integration with Existing Systems: Integrate face recognition with existing CCTV infrastructure for seamless operation and monitoring.\n ├ö├ç├│ Automated Alerts: Implement an automated alert system to notify officers immediately when a match for a missing person or item is detected.\n \n 2. Enhanced Communication Systems:\n ├ö├ç├│ Centralized Communication Platform: Establish a centralized platform for real-time communication and information sharing among police units.\n ├ö├ç├│ Mobile Connectivity: Provide mobile connectivity solutions to ensure that officers on the ground can receive and relay information quickly.\n ├ö├ç├│ Data Sharing with Public: Set up a system for real-time data sharing with the public, enabling individuals to report missing persons or items and receive updates.\n \n 3. Training and Support:\n ├ö├ç├│ Comprehensive Training: Provide training to police officers on using face recognition technology and the new communication systems effectively.\n ├ö├ç├│ Technical Support: Ensure continuous technical support for the maintenance and troubleshooting of the deployed systems.\n 4. Privacy and Security Measures:\n ├ö├ç├│ Data Privacy: Implement robust data privacy measures to protect the personal information of individuals captured by the face recognition system.\n ├ö├ç├│ Security Protocols: Establish security protocols to safeguard the surveillance and communication systems from unauthorized access and misuse.\n By addressing these challenges with the implementation of face recognition surveillance and enhanced communication systems, the police department can significantly improve its ability to manage large crowds, ensure public safety, and respond promptly to reports of missing persons or items during Simhasth Ujjain.\n </div>\n                               </td>\n                            </tr>\n\n                            <tr>\n                                <th>Organization</th>\n                            <td>Madhya Pradesh Police </td>\n                                            \n                            </tr>  \n                            \n                            <tr>\n                                <th>Department</th>\n                            <td>Madhya Pradesh Police </td>\n                                            \n                            </tr>  \n\n                            <tr>\n                            <th>Category</th>\n                            <td>Software</td>\n                            </tr>\n\n                            <tr>\n                            <th>Theme</th>\n                            <td>Smart Automation</td>\n                            </tr>\n                            <tr>\n                              <th>Youtube Link</th>\n                              <td>\n                                    <a href=\" \" target=\"_blank\"> </a>\n                            </td>  \n                            </tr> \n                                                      <tr>\n                              <th>Dataset Link</th>\n                              <td>\n                                <br>\n                                 <!-- <a href=\"https://www.sih.gov.in/uploads/psData/\"><br></a> -->\n                                                                                          </td>  \n                            </tr>\n                            <tr>\n                              <th>Contact info</th>\n                              <td>\n                                    <a href=\" \" target=\"_blank\"> </a>\n                            </td>  \n                            </tr> \n    \n                      </thead>\n                     </table>",
